<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,484,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Distributional remarks.</emphasis>
The above description was based on three female specimens, males are unknown. This species was described based on specimens collected in the nineteenth century, deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[1259,1348,440,463]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">MNHN</collectionCode>
. So far, extensive sampling in some parts of the Atlantic forest located in 
<collectingRegion box="[886,951,476,501]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Bahia</collectingRegion>
state (
<typeStatus box="[1025,1075,476,500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">type</typeStatus>
locality) has provided no recent specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-De-Mello &amp; Silva, 2017" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2017" box="[312,410,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scybalocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batesi" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis box="[312,410,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. batesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[420,506,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[420,506,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">sp. nov</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
.. Thus, as the Atlantic rainforest (supposed habitat for this species) is a greatly threatened habitat and the last known record for this species was from 1892, there was good reason to consider 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-De-Mello &amp; Silva, 2017" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scybalocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">S. batesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[228,322,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[228,315,583,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
critically endangered or presumed extinct according to 
<collectionCode box="[978,1046,584,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List Categories and Criteria (
<collectionCode box="[158,231,620,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">IUCN</collectionCode>
